wikipedia_page.main: June Elizabeth Edney (née Law; born 27 April 1956) is an English former cricketer who played as a right-handed batter and wicket-keeper. She appeared in 8 Test matches and 6 One Day Internationals for England between 1984 and 1985. She played domestic cricket for Kent.
